ipaddress module verbatim from cpython tag v3.4.0

Version 2.0.1: Fix excessive memory consumption in hosts() etc.

Python 2's range allocates a list of the entire range (e.g. 17 million
elements for `IPv4Network('10.0.0.0/8').hosts()`).  Python 3's range
corresponds to Python 2's xrange.
Specify correct license (PSF license, not Apache; fixes #1)
Version 2.0: New backport by Roman Klesel, more accurately matching Python 3.3.
Use only new-style (Python 3-style) classes.
Clean-up: Remove excessive whitespace and unused variables and imports.
Unitests taken from Python3.3 and ported to Python2.6+

Total rework against the current version found in Python3.3 source.

Note: The version found at https://code.google.com/p/ipaddress-py/source/browse/ipaddress.py is outdated and has been changed a lot by the python people
py2-ipaddress: Python 2.7 backport of 3.3's ipaddress module.
